'''崔杋圭'''（{{kor|k=최범규|rm=Choi Beom-gyu}}，{{bd|2001年|3月13日|catIdx=C}}），藝名為'''BEOMGYU'''（{{lang-ko|범규}}；{{lang-ja|ボムギュー}}）。[[韓國|韓國]][[男歌手|男歌手]]，為[[韓國|韓國]][[男子團體|男子團體]][[TXT_(組合)|TOMORROW X TOGETHER]]年紀排行第三的成員，為最後公開的[[TXT_(組合)|TOMORROW X TOGETHER]]成員。<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.kpopn.com/2019/01/21/bts-younger-brother-boy-group-txt-5th-member-beomgyu|title=BTS 師弟團 TXT 第五位成員 BEOMGYU 宣傳照、宣傳影片公開！|accessdate=2019-01-21|work=Kpopn|language=zh-hant|archive-date=2020-10-02|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201002031826/https://www.kpopn.com/2019/01/21/bts-younger-brother-boy-group-txt-5th-member-beomgyu|dead-url=no}}</ref>2019年3月4日，透過迷你專輯《[[The_Dream_Chapter:_STAR|The Dream Chapter: STAR]]》於[[韓國|韓國]]出道。<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://entertain.naver.com/read?oid=057&aid=0001324678|title=투모로우바이투게더, 3월4일 Mnet ‘데뷔 셀러브레이션 쇼’로 데뷔(공식입장)|accessdate=2019-02-07|work=MBN|language=ko|archive-date=2019-02-09|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190209124507/https://entertain.naver.com/read?oid=057&aid=0001324678|dead-url=no}}</ref>2020年1月15日，透過[[日本|日本]]出道單曲《[[MAGIC_HOUR|MAGIC HOUR]]》於[[日本|日本]]出道。<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.kpopn.com/2020/01/19/txt-japan-music-station|title=2020第一組韓國藝人！TXT 將登日《MUSIC STATION》演出|accessdate=2020-01-19|work=|language=zh-hant|archive-date=2020-02-13|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200213174240/https://www.kpopn.com/2020/01/19/txt-japan-music-station|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.koreastardaily.com/tc/news/123731|title=TXT 進軍日本傳捷報　出道單曲奪 Oricon 榜冠軍！|accessdate=2020-01-22|work=|language=zh-hant|archive-date=2020-02-13|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200213174251/https://www.koreastardaily.com/tc/news/123731|dead-url=no}}</ref>

== 生涯 == 
===出道前===
家中成員有父母以及一位哥哥。{{NoteTag|出道特別節目《Debut Celebration Show》自介中敘述，參見<ref name="TMI 1">{{Citation|last=Mnet K-POP|title=[TMI 프로필 Part.1] 리더 수빈, 맏형 연준, 하이텐션 범규 {{!}} DEBUT CELEBRATION SHOW|date=2019-03-04|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=D8nNzMaXGxA|accessdate=2019-04-08|archive-date=2022-03-03|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220303035338/https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=D8nNzMaXGxA}}</ref>}}中學時曾是樂隊成員，因此能夠演奏吉他以及電子吉他。<ref>{{Citation|last=TOMORROW X TOGETHER|title=【TXT】崔范奎中学时期电吉他表演完整版|date=2019-02-17|url=https://www.bilibili.com/video/BV1Rb411y7ko|accessdate=2020-04-10|archive-date=2020-10-01|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201001202014/https://www.bilibili.com/video/BV1Rb411y7ko|dead-url=no}}</ref>2018年8月，在練習生時期曾與團員共同在[[美國|美國]]培訓。{{NoteTag|2019年4月8日官方社群Instagram限時動態透露，參見<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.instagram.com/stories/highlights/17858945044373432/|title=2018년 8월|accessdate=2019-04-08|work=txt_bighit|language=ko|archive-date=2020-11-01|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201101124419/https://www.instagram.com/stories/highlights/17858945044373432/}}</ref>}}

===2019年：韓國出道===
1月20日，所屬社釋出了BEOMGYU概念照及影片。<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://metro.co.uk/2019/01/21/beomgyu-fifth-member-k-pop-group-txt-8369265/|title=Who is Beomgyu, the fifth member of K-pop group TXT?|accessdate=2019-01-21|work=|language=en|archive-date=2020-04-11|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200411095743/https://metro.co.uk/2019/01/21/beomgyu-fifth-member-k-pop-group-txt-8369265/|dead-url=no}}</ref>

3月4日，透過[[Mnet|Mnet]]的慶祝出道特輯節目《TOMORROW X TOGETHER Debut Celebration Show presented by Mnet》於[[韓國|韓國]]正式出道，並發行首張迷你專輯《[[The_Dream_Chapter:_STAR|The Dream Chapter: STAR]]》。<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.txtuniverse.com/feed/board/1/detail/13240|title=TOMORROW X TOGETHER 데뷔 안내|accessdate=2019-02-07|work=TXTUniverse|language=ko|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190209124548/https://www.txtuniverse.com/feed/board/1/detail/13240|archive-date=2019-02-09|dead-url=yes}}</ref>

===2020年：日本出道===
1月15日，以[[TXT_(組合)|TOMORROW X TOGETHER]]成員發行出道單曲《[[MAGIC_HOUR|MAGIC HOUR]]》於[[日本|日本]]出道。<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.monstersandcritics.com/music/kpop/txt-japanese-debut-magic-hour-takes-number-one-on-japanese-oricon-daily-singles-chart-to-be-first-korean-performer-of-2020-on-japans-music-station/|title=TXT Japanese debut: Magic Hour takes number one on Japanese Oricon Daily Singles Chart, to be first Korean performer of 2020 on Japan’s Music Station|accessdate=2020-01-19|work=|language=en|archive-date=2020-04-11|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200411095719/https://www.monstersandcritics.com/music/kpop/txt-japanese-debut-magic-hour-takes-number-one-on-japanese-oricon-daily-singles-chart-to-be-first-korean-performer-of-2020-on-japans-music-station/|dead-url=no}}</ref>

